tion:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/the-terrorism-act\">the Terrorism Act</a></div></div>\n","matches":["the Prevention of Terrorism Act"],"relatives":["the Prevention of Terrorism Act"],"nearBys":["terror noun","terrorism noun","the Terrorism Act","terrorist noun","terrorize verb"]},{"name":"the Prevention of Terrorism Act","pos":"adjective","content":"<div class=\"entry\" htag=\"section\" id=\"the-prevention-of-terrorism-act\" hlength=\"31\" sk=\"preventionofterrorismact: :15\" sum=\"921\" hclass=\"entry\" idm_id=\"000046645\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"the_prevention_of_terrorism_act_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" htag=\"h1\" id=\"the_prevention_of_terrorism_act_h_1\" hclass=\"headword\"><span class=\"st\" id=\"the_prevention_of_terrorism_act_st_1\">the</span> Prevention of Terrorism Act</h1> <span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" wd=\"the Prevention of Terrorism Act\" hclass=\"phons_br\" geo=\"br\" htag=\"div\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/p/pre/preve/prevention_of_terrorism_act_1_gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/p/pre/preve/prevention_of_terrorism_act_1_gb_1.ogg\" title=\"the Prevention of Terrorism Act pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ðə prɪˌvenʃn əv ˈterərɪzəm ækt/</span></div> <div class=\"phons_n_am\" htag=\"div\" geo=\"n_am\" wd=\"the Prevention of Terrorism Act\" hclass=\"phons_n_am\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-us icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron/p/pre/preve/prevention_of_terrorism_act_1_us_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron_ogg/p/pre/preve/prevention_of_terrorism_act_1_us_1.ogg\" title=\"the Prevention of Terrorism Act pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ðə prɪˌvenʃn əv ˈterərɪzəm ækt/</span></div></span></div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" id=\"preventionofterrorismact_sng_1\" htag=\"li\" hclass=\"sense\"><a class=\"open oup_icons\" title=\"Add to My Word Lists\"><span class=\"star-btn\" aria-hidden=\"true\">​</span></a><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\">a British <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/act-of-parliament\" title=\"Act of Parliament definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Act of Parliament</span></a> introduced on a temporary basis in 1984 to prevent <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/terrorism\" title=\"terrorism definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">terrorism</span></a> <span class=\"gloss\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"gloss\">(= the use of violence for political aims)</span> in Northern Ireland. It gave the police the power to arrest anyone suspected of <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/terrorist\" title=\"terrorist definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">terrorist</span></a> activities and to hold them for 48 hours without giving a reason. It was replaced in 2000 by the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-terrorism-act#the_terrorism_act_topg_1\" title=\"Terrorism Act definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Terrorism Act</span></a> which had changes made to it by the Anti-terrorism, Crime and Security Act of 2001. In 2005 a new <span class=\"dh\">Prevention of Terrorism Act</span> was passed which gave the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/home-secretary\" title=\"Home Secretary definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Home Secretary</span></a> the power to use <span class=\"ei\">control orders</span> to limit the freedom of people suspected of terrorism. This Act was later judged in a court to go against the individual's right to a fair trial under the European Convention on Human Rights, and it was <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/repeal_2\" title=\"repealed definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">repealed</span></a> <span class=\"gloss\" hclass=\"gloss\" htag=\"span\">(= cancelled)</span> in 2011.</span></span>    \n</li></ol><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/the-prevention-of-terrorism-act\">the Prevention of Terrorism Act</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["preventable adjective","prevention noun","the Prevention of Terrorism Act","preventive adjective","preverbal adjective"]},{"name":"the Terrorism Act","pos":"adjective","content":"<div class=\"entry\" hclass=\"entry\" sum=\"855\" sk=\"terrorismact: :15\" htag=\"section\" hlength=\"17\" id=\"the-terrorism-act\" idm_id=\"000060627\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"the_terrorism_act_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" hclass=\"headword\" id=\"the_terrorism_act_h_1\" htag=\"h1\"><span class=\"st\" id=\"the_terrorism_act_st_1\">the</span> Terrorism Act</h1> <span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" htag=\"div\" geo=\"br\" wd=\"the Terrorism Act\" hclass=\"phons_br\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/t/ter/terro/terrorism_act_1_gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com